import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['origin'] = data['origin'].astype('category')
    data['destination'] = data['destination'].astype('category')
    sns.countplot(x='origin', data=data, color='blue', label='Origin')
    sns.countplot(x='destination', data=data, color='red', label='Destination')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the busiest airport in terms of origin and destination?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    data['origin'] = data['origin'].astype('category')
    data['destination'] = data['destination'].astype('category')
    delay_by_origin = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].mean().reset_index()
    delay_by_destination = data.groupby('destination')['delay'].mean().reset_index()
    delay_by_origin.columns = ['airport', 'average_delay']
    delay_by_destination.columns = ['airport', 'average_delay']
    delay_by_origin['direction'] = 'origin'
    delay_by_destination['direction'] = 'destination'
    delay_by_airport = pd.concat([delay_by_origin, delay_by_destination])
    ax = sns.barplot(x='airport', y='average_delay', hue='direction', data=delay_by_airport)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average delay time for each airport?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='count'))
    ax.set(xlabel='Date', ylabel='Count')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
